				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\text{E}}_{\text{LUMO}} = {\text{E}}_{\text{HOMO}} + {\text{E}}_{\text{g}}^{\text{opt}}$$\end{document} [19–21]. Exactly 0.1 M of lithium perchlorate (LiClO4) was used as the supporting electrolyte. On the basis of the HOMO–LUMO levels presented in Table 2, Fig. 7 presents a schematic diagram for comparing the energy levels of the investigated sensitizers in terms of vacuum level and normal hydrogen electrode (NHE).Fig. 6
